# Leads Nexus Project Structure

This is a monorepo with the following structure:

## Applications
- **`apps/web/`** - Next.js web application with React 19 + TypeScript 5.7
- **`apps/native/`** - React Native/Expo mobile application
- **`apps/server/`** - tRPC server with Drizzle ORM
- **`apps/docs/`** - Astro documentation site

## Key Files & Directories
- **Root**: [package.json](mdc:package.json), [turbo.json](mdc:turbo.json), [biome.json](mdc:biome.json)
- **Web App**: [apps/web/src/app/layout.tsx](mdc:apps/web/src/app/layout.tsx), [apps/web/next.config.ts](mdc:apps/web/next.config.ts)
- **Native App**: [apps/native/app/_layout.tsx](mdc:apps/native/app/_layout.tsx), [apps/native/app.json](mdc:apps/native/app.json)
- **Server**: [apps/server/src/index.ts](mdc:apps/server/src/index.ts), [apps/server/drizzle.config.ts](mdc:apps/server/drizzle.config.ts)
- **Docs**: [apps/docs/astro.config.mjs](mdc:apps/docs/astro.config.mjs)

## Development Flow
1. Always check the specific app directory for context
2. Use tRPC for client-server communication
3. Shared utilities in `packages/` (when created)
4. UI components in respective app directories
